data.title: Event Listing
data.meta_description: Meany Center for the Performing Arts (formerly UW World Series) at the University of Washington fosters innovative performances that advance public engagement, cultural exchange, creative research and learning through the arts. Meany Center provides opportunities for diverse artists, community, students and faculty to connect in the discovery and exploration of the boundless
data.text:
Theater and cirque meet the mat to celebrate the exuberant nature of wrestling in a spectacular display of acrobatics and strength.

Curated by Artistic Partner Rhiannon Giddens, the group exemplifies the contemporary identity of Irish music and the positive impact of migration on culture.

This superstar’s exquisite artistry bridges traditions from across the Americas, with folk and ranchera music of Mexico and South America to North American folk, jazz, blues and hip-hop.

Three virtuosos of violin, cello and bass deliver an innovative program of new works and timeless music.

In re:CREATION the boundaries of gravity and creativity blur in a dynamic collection of timeless works, groundbreaking new experiments and inventive collaborations.

Curated by Artistic Partner Rhiannon Giddens. Two powerhouse Indigenous artists come together to share their artistry with music that honors their ancestral roots and lives vibrantly in the present.

Beloved pianist brings his profound musical depth to explore the theme of fantasies in works by Schumann, Beethoven and Corigliano.

Two Clowns: Pierrot Meets Petrushka celebrates Schoenberg, Stravinsky and Ravel with an ensemble of some of today’s most distinguished musicians in concert.

The Grammy-winning duo brings their dynamic energy to a wondrous mixture of bluegrass and holiday classics that capture the holiday spirit.

The British vocal ensemble’s Winter Tales features thoughtful religious themes by Bach and Britten and holiday favorites that celebrate the season.

Dancing en travesti with razor-sharp wit and breathtaking pointe work, the all-male company performs polished parodies of pieces that span the classical ballet canon.

Kodō’s taiko drumming explores the limitless possibilities of the traditional Japanese drum, forging new directions for a vibrant living art form.

The diverse music of Counterpoint combines dance and piano artistry that drives the imagination and opens the heart for a unique Valentine’s Day performance.

Family of sarod virtuosos showcasing the rich tradition of Indian classical and folk music with elegant lyricism and joy-filled dynamism.

The Quartet’s vision to revisit, rediscover and reinvigorate the repertory features works by Mozart and Beethoven plus a reflection on unrequited love by jazz pianist Billy Childs.

Founded by Ronald K. Brown, EVIDENCE focuses on the seamless integration of traditional African dance with contemporary choreography and spoken word.

The imaginative pianist brings his virtuosic dexterity and creativity to Bach’s Six Partitas for Keyboard, known for being as technically difficult as they are beautiful.

Curated by Artistic Partner Rhiannon Giddens. A stunning collaboration brings together a collection of distinctive and powerful musical origins within a contemporary musical tapestry.

The company presents Deep River, a soulful collaboration that bends the lines between classical and contemporary dance while drawing from deeply rooted cultural traditions.
